Single line comments start with #

Indentation must be done properly

Here is a summary of the conventions that have been discussed:

End multi line comments with ''' on a line by itself
Use " for strings instead of ' (This is the convention we'll use for class, but the other way would be acceptable. Consistency is the key)
Use four space instead of a tab (PyCharm automatically uses spaces when you hit the tab button)
Place spaces around arithmetic symbols (except for unary +/-)
Use blank lines to separate code for understanding
Variable and function names should be lowerCamelCase (first letter lowercase and first letter of each additional word is uppercase)
Note: all_lowercase is another common convention. We will use lowerCamelCase in this class to be consistent with the book
Variable names should be nouns
Function names should be verbs
Constant names should be ALL_UPPERCASE

Let user enter name, hours worked, hourly wage, and federal and state tax rates.

System analysis
    weekly gross pay = numHours * wage
    fed witholding = gross pay * (pct/100)
    state witholding = gross pay * (pct/100)
    total deduction = fed + state
    net pay = gross pay - total deduction
